OL,6,F"Today's sentencing shows that we, as
OL,7,Fa force, will relentlessly pursue
OL,8,Fthose who perpetrate violence against
OL,9,Fwomen and girls and bring them to
OL,10,Fjustice."
OL,12,FIn a statement read to the court Ms
OL,13,FBrown said: "I suffer flashbacks and
OL,14,Fnightmares and can still feel pain
OL,15,Fwhen Darren stabbed me.
OL,17,F"I know Darren was hurting. But I
OL,18,Fdidn't deserve what he did to me. He
OL,19,Fcould have walked away got help.
OL,20,FInstead he stabbed me a third time and
OL,21,Fleft me for dead.
